1:1 COMMENT "# narrowing.z -- Type narrowing for union and variant types"
1:60 EOL "\n"
2:1 COMMENT "# Demonstrates compile-time type narrowing via match and assignment."
2:69 EOL "\n"
3:1 COMMENT "#"
3:2 EOL "\n"
4:1 COMMENT "# There are two narrowing modes:"
4:33 EOL "\n"
5:1 COMMENT "#   1. Assignment-based: `a: result.ok 42` leaves `a` typed as the"
5:67 EOL "\n"
6:1 COMMENT "#      full `result`; a `narrowed_subtype` sidecar permits `a.ok` and"
6:70 EOL "\n"
7:1 COMMENT "#      rejects accessing other arms (`a.err` is an error)."
7:59 EOL "\n"
8:1 COMMENT "#   2. Match-arm (shadow): inside `case ok then { ... }`, the matched"
8:70 EOL "\n"
9:1 COMMENT "#      name IS the payload \u{2014} bare `b` reads the payload directly."
9:66 EOL "\n"
10:1 COMMENT "#      Reaching back to the parent arm (`b.ok`) is an error."
10:61 EOL "\n"
11:1 EOL "\n"
